title: For Sale:  Taurus PT-140 complete.
postcontent:
It'll include the gun, a magazine the case and a nylon brush. 

This is a real good conceal carry gun and even with it's higher power charge has a very sustainable recoil. When I swapped the Guy for this I was skeptical about it even cycling, took it to the range and put 150 rounds down w/o a hitch. It's pretty easy to clean, not quite as easy to strip apart as a Glock but as long as the barrel is recessed a tad it gives you no problems. The reason I want to sell it is I'm not a fan of the trigger. Its got a little more creep then I like, and I've got my eye settled on Ruger Blackhawk. This is going to help fund that. I've put 150 rounds out, and the previous owner did not mention. If I had to guess it's had between 500 and 1000 rounds so theres still plenty of life left. These are going on GB for $410+ S&H and a FFL fee to pick it up of $20. You're looking at over $450 for one off the internet and probably $420ish in a store for a new one. I feel $340 is a fair price for this one and after seeing it I'm confident you will too. 

You've got to be 21 to buy. I'm not driving all over the State for $340 so if Bass Pro in Cincinnati mall is to far I appreciate you looking at the ad. I'm not interested in shipping. And the only trades I'd consider will have to be absolute steals. I.E. Smith and Wesson .500 complete w/ scope. If its close or a slight trade up/down I wont consider it. I really want my Ruger Blackhawk.

title: For Sale:  Kahr MK40 40S&W subcompact
postcontent:
Like new Kahr MK40 subcompact semiautomatic pistol, in nickel finish.  Great gun for backup or pocket carry, and shoots softer than you'd expect due to its captive double recoil spring (licensed from Seecamp).  It also has a very nice smooth DAO trigger pull.  I put about 100 rounds through it right after I bought it, but other than carrying it a few times I haven't done much else with it.

I have average size hands and I can get a solid 2-finger grip with the flush magazine.  The extended mag makes the grip length a non-issue.

Comes with original 2 magazines (1 5-round flush and 1 6-roudn extended), and I'll throw in 2 more mags I bought last year (never used).

The manufacturer's website has more info and an excellent review:
http://www.kahr.com/PA-1B/review_gm_0400.html

The SPAS-12 is a combat shotgun that was manufactured by the Italian firearms company Franchi S.p.A. from 1979 to 2000.
